related_questions.question: What happens in the Book of Job?
related_questions.snippet: Summary. Job is a wealthy man living in a land called Uz with his large family and extensive flocks. ... God boasts to Satan about Job's goodness, but Satan argues that Job is only good because God has blessed him abundantly. Satan challenges God that, if given permission to punish the man, Job will turn and curse God.

related_questions.snippet: The Talmud (redacted at about 500 CE) has several versions.
